        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Using the gas models reported in Bradac et al. 2006, the jump in Compton-y at the shock front is over 1.4e-4, corresponding to 53 microJy/bm in a 5" FWHM beam. The proposed observations, which aim 
for a sensitivity of 7.6 microJy/bm, will 
therefore test the shock model at a signal to noise of &gt;7 (or S/N &gt; 5 when allowing for the lower 1-sigma error allowed by the X-ray model for the shock).  Complementary observations with the ACA will recover larger scales and probe to a lower average Compton-y, though at lower resolution, enabling better imaging of the shock front</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
